.TH "drm_gem_vram_create" 9 "drm_gem_vram_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_vram_create \- Creates a VRAM-backed GEM object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_gem_vram_object *" drm_gem_vram_create
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pg_align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the DRM device
.IP "size" 12
the buffer size in bytes
.IP "pg_align" 12
the buffer's alignment in multiples of the page size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
GEM objects are allocated by calling struct drm_driver.gem_create_object,
if set. Otherwise \fBkzalloc\fP will be used. Drivers can set their own GEM
object functions in struct drm_driver.gem_create_object. If no functions
are set, the new GEM object will use the default functions from GEM VRAM
helpers.
.SH "RETURN"
A new instance of \fIstruct drm_gem_vram_object\fP on success, or
an \fBERR_PTR\fP-encoded error code otherwise.
